          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "justification": "Three conjuncts license the gBGC-scar conclusion: (1) absolute Cohen's d > 1.0 establishes a 'large' effect by Cohen's convention; (2) the sign must be positive (OLD > YOUNG), encoding the directional gBGC prediction — a negative d at the same magnitude would falsify the gBGC framework, not support it; (3) raw mean GC ordering must match (redundant with #2 but defensive against d-computation bugs).",
    "failure_mode": "If s_cohens_d_gc were negative or near zero, the material-channel record of recombination history would not exist at this resolution. Old hotspots being GC-DEPLETED (negative d) would falsify the gBGC scar; old hotspots being indistinguishable from young (|d| < 0.5) would suggest the scar is below the 1 Mb resolution floor."
  },
  "conclusion": {
    "assertion": "At 1 Mb autosomal resolution, top-quartile crossover-rate windows that are also top-quartile in 241-way phyloP conservation (proxy for OLD hotspots) have mean GC = 47.1%, vs 39.6% for young hotspots (top crossover rate AND bottom-quartile conservation), Cohen's d = +1.76. The directional gBGC-scar prediction is confirmed in the material channel.",
